This is an image-less, stylesheet *only* theme. You need to make a "theme"
directory in the ROOTDIR of your site and copy this folder, in it's entirety,
to the "theme" directory.  After that, just run bblog, select "5" for the
Settings menu, then select "3" for "Change theme" and select the number beside
"Badge" in the browser menu.  That's all there is to it. 

Just so there's not confusion, here's an example assuming /var/www as the
ROOTDIR:

user@domain:/home/user/Desktop/bblog-0.3.6/Badge$ mkdir -p /var/www/theme
user@domain:/home/user/Desktop/bblog-0.3.6/Badge$ cd .. && cp -R Badge /var/www/theme
user@domain:/home/user/Desktop/bblog-0.3.6/$ bblog

  +--------------------------------------------------------------+
  | BashBlogger-0.3.6                                  Main Menu |
  +--------------------------------------------------------------+
  1.) Articles                         4.) Links
  2.) Drafts                           5.) Settings
  3.) Pages
 
 
  Select [ 1 - 6 | x to exit ] : 5


  +--------------------------------------------------------------+
  | BashBlogger-0.3.6                                   Settings |
  +--------------------------------------------------------------+
  1.) Edit settings                   5.) Import RSS
  2.) Edit CSS                        6.) Export RSS
  3.) Change theme                    7.) Synchronize Remote
  4.) Rebuild site
 
 
  Select [ 1 - 7 | x to exit ] : 3


  +--------------------------------------------------------------+
  | BashBlogger-0.3.6                              Theme Manager |
  +--------------------------------------------------------------+
  1) Badge 

  Select [ 1 - 1 | x to exit ] and hit enter : 1


You can delete this README out of the directory (if you want).  It won't hurt
anything to leave this README in the copied folder. 
